"(1) (i) stood motionless on the glass-steel catwalk of ’s sublevel-7, the sterile white light of the artificial dawn filtering through the dome’s iridescent film to paint the control chamber in shifting emerald and violet hues, her breath fogging in the recycled air as the hum of the dormant matter synthesizer thrummed through the floor plates and she felt the weight of a thousand unsolved equations pressing in on her as the readouts flashed crimson and the containment field shuddered, her mind racing through the protocols she’d studied but never truly understood as alarms crescendoed and the machine’s core pulsed with a light so bright it momentarily drowned out the stars visible through the observatory’s primary viewport, her fingers trembling as she watched the data streams spiral into chaos, knowing with sudden, icy clarity that the overload was inevitable and yet powerless to halt it. Mercury Twilight Observatory. October 13, 2224. Brooklyn Ross. witnessed a matter synthesizer overload."